e in the 1980s. By 2001, the company competed with the major Hollywood studios and reached global box office success with the Lord of the Rings franchise. Blurring boundaries between high and low culture, between independent film and Hollywood, and between the margins and the mainstream, New Line Cinema epitomizes Hollywood's shift in focus from the mass audience fostered by the classic studios to the multitude of niche audiences sought today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture studiosxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion picture studiosxHistoryy21st century. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520382367zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520382367zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520382367/original  a978-3-11-079134-1 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA